     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "150\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "calc_sum(10, 20, 30, 40, 50)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example: Temperature Conversion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- The following program convert the temperature from degrees Celsius to degrees Fahrenheit."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def input_temp():\n",
    "    temp = float(input('Enter the temperature in °C: '))\n",
    "    return temp\n",
    "\n",
    "def convert_temp(c):\n",
    "    f = 9/5 * c + 32\n",
    "    return f\n",
    "    \n",
    "def output_temp(f):\n",
    "    print('The temperature is', f, '°F.')\n",
    "    \n",
    "def main():\n",
    "    c = input_temp()\n",
    "    f = convert_temp(c)\n",
    "    output_temp(f)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Enter the temperature in °C: 100\n",
      "The temperature is 212.0 °F.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "main()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "212.0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 14,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "convert_temp(100)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Save the code as a Python file/script/module/program: `c2f.py`.\n",
    "- Open it in the Jupyter editor.\n",
    "- What is the deal with the last two lines of `c2f.py`?\n",
    "```python\n",
    "if __name__ == '__main__':\n",
    "    main()\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- The special variable `__name__` (`__`is pronounce ['dunder'](https://wiki.python.org/moin/DunderAlias)) determines whether a module is imported or run directly.\n",
    "- If the file is run directly, the value of `__name__` is `'__main__'`.\n",
    "- If the file is imported, `__name__` represents the file's name."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Run the file in Jupyter Notebook directly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
